00003 Radial profiles of $L_{
u_e}$ and $L_{ ar{
u}_e}$ during the early accretion phase ($70 \, \mathrm{ms}$ after bounce) for model s27. The hierarchy of the luminosities at infinity $L_{
u_e} > L_{ ar{
u}_e}$ is inverted compared to the luminosities just outside the proto-neutron star ($r \approx 90 \, \mathrm{km}$), because emission dominates over absorption for electron neutrinos in the post-shock region, while the electron antineutrino luminosity is reduced considerably between $90 \, \mathrm{km}$ and $140 \, \mathrm{km}$ due to net absorption. The kink at $\sim 140 \, \mathrm{km}$ coincides with the shock position and is an artifact of the transformation from the comoving frame to the lab frame.

00008 Time evolution of the electron antineutrino mean energy $\langle E_{ ar{
u}_e} angle / (M / M_\odot)$ rescaled by the proto-neutron star mass $M$ for the different progenitors. The mean energies $\langle E_{ ar{
u}_e} angle$ themselves are shown as dashed lines along with the rescaled mean energies $\langle E_{ ar{
u}_e} angle / (M / M_\odot)$ (solid lines). When comparing different progenitors the reader should note that models s11.2 and s15s7b2 have been computed with an angular resolution of $2.8^\circ$ instead of $1.4^\circ$ (u8.1, z9.6, s25, s27), and that two different EoS's have been used (u8.1, s11.2, s15s7b2: LS180; z9.6, s25, s27: LS 220).
